<h1>Best Ways To Protect Your AC</h1>

Air conditioner has become the necessary electronics items which have become very common and are found in homes and offices in the hot summer season all over the country. The main reason of popularity of the air conditioning unit is the escalating temperature outside any premises, which affects the people inside the premises. Before some year, the air conditioner could be afforded only by the affluent sections of the city. Today, with rising income, most of the households and the offices have some type of AC such as cube ac to cool the room as per the choice of the users. But, like any other electronics item, the user has to guard their air conditioners from various threats such as theft, rains and winter. The owner should use some methods to guard the air conditioner from these threats.<br />
<br />
<strong>The Best Methods<br />
</strong><br />
<ol type="1"><li> Check the air conditioning circuit of the commercial ac which has been installed in your premises. Most of the time, the electrical circuit is covered with metal lid or the plastic lid. With the arrival of winter season, you should flip the lid open and switch off the unit. With this action, you can prevent the switching on the air conditioning unit during the warm winter day. It will also keep out the water, which can freeze inside the unit in winter season.
</li><li> You should wash the split ac with the water hose to remove the dirt which includes the dust, bird droppings, dead bugs etc. You should also remove the grass clippings, small branches and leaves from the unit. Before switching on the ac unit, you should allow it to dry completely. Also, always try to keep it clean.
</li><li> Make sure to install the foam pipe around the exposed pipes which are outside the premises. For that, you have to cut the foam which will fit the diameter and the length of the pipe. The foam covers helps for the insulation of the pipe. It also protects the pipe from the low temperature in winter season. To hold them in the place, you have to wrap the duct tape. The cover also protects the pipe from rusting.
</li><li> Always cover the air conditioner with vinyl or plastic cover. You should choose a cover which is waterproof.
</li><li> Always make a check on the air conditioner every week about the security of the cover. Always brush off the dirt, dust and water from the top of the cover.</li></ol>
Make Sure to check <a class="ext" href="https://www.bestgreenac.in/ultimate-guide-to-buying-acs/">AC buying guide in India</a><span class="exttail">&#8734;</span> before you purchase any AC.</div>
